      "published_date": "2025-08-24T00:00:00.000Z",
      "text": "Revised on 8/24/2025\nHOSTING CAPACITY TOOL (HCT) \nUSER INTERFACE GUIDE AND FAQS\nSouthwest Power Pool, Inc.\nREVISION HISTORY\nDATE AUTHOR CHANGE DESCRIPTION\n2/6/2025 IT Engineering Staff Created an initial document for UIs available in\nthe Hosting Capacity Tool.\n5/9/2025 Generator \nInterconnection Staff\nCombined User Guide and FAQ documents.\n8/24/2025 Generator \nInterconnection Staff\nAdditional information about HCT and \nunderlying assumptions\nSouthwest Power Pool, Inc.\n1\nCONTENTS\nREVISION HISTORY..........................................................................................................................................................I\nBACKGROUND .................................................................................................................................................................2\nHCT OVERVIEW AT HTTPS://PST.SPP.ORG/..........................................................................................................3\nMODELS AND ASSUMPTIONS....",
      "highlights": [
        "2/6/2025 IT Engineering Staff Created an initial document for UIs available in\nthe Hosting Capacity Tool. 5/9/2025 Generator \nInterconnection Staff\nCombined User Guide and FAQ documents.\n8/24/2025 Generator Interconnection Staff\nAdditional information about HCT and \nunderlying assumptions\nSouthwest Power Pool, Inc.\n1  ...    HCT OVERVIEW AT HTTPS://PST.SPP.ORG/..........................................................................................................3 MODELS AND ASSUMPTIONS...................................................................................................................................4 DISIS-2023-001 PHASE 2 STUDY ASSUMPTION INFORMATION.................................................................5 HTTPS://PST.SPP.ORG/  ...    Status Message Colors.................................................................................................................  ...    The SPP Hosting Capacity Tool (HCT) was developed from requirements under SCRIPT which was to reimagine SPP’s transmission planning process. The Consolidated Planning Process (CPP) will bring the Integrated Transmission Planning (ITP) and Generator Interconnection (GI) studies together into one process. Through SCRIPT and CPP, there is a need for new tools to assist customers. The goal of the Hosting Capacity Tool is to provide data on capacity of the existing  ...    facility after the injection of the proposed project.\nSouthwest Power Pool, Inc.\n3\nHCT OVERVIEW AT HTTPS://PST.SPP.ORG/\nITP Legacy, ITP Non-Legacy, Prior Queue (PQ), and Current Queue (CQ) generation definitions can be found in GI MANUAL BUSINESS PRACTICE 7250.\nSouthwest Power Pool, Inc.\n4\nMODELS AND ASSUMPTIONS The SPP Hosting Capacity Tool (HCT) uses the most recent posted DISIS Steady-State Year 2 Current Queue (CQ) models with the lowest queued Interconnection Requests. More  ...    ERIS (GROUP 1, 2, 3, 4, 5) Models\nDIS231TC01ALL-24SP\nDIS231TC02ALL-24SP\nDIS231TC03ALL-24SP\nDIS231TC04ALL-24SP  ...    https://opsportal.spp.org/documents/studies/files/2023_Generation_Studies/FINAL\u0002DISIS_Results_Workbook_DIS2301-P2-Power  ...    Model assumptions to include a gen list with Current Queue (CQ), Prior Queue (PQ), and Non\u0002Legacy ITP Firm and Non-Firm generation requests and worksheet with previously assigned transmission upgrades in models can be found with the Base model set.\nSouthwest Power Pool, Inc.\n1 HTTPS://PST.SPP.ORG/ WALKTHROUGH\nSouthwest Power Pool, Inc.\n1\nABOUT THIS GUIDE\nPURPOSE The purpose of this document is to provide a user interface (UI) reference guide for users utilizing the Hosting Capacity Tool (HCT), which is a Pre-screening Tool (PST) for external users. This guide describes how to create a new user account and generate a  ...    o Exporting the Table Data\nSouthwest Power Pool, Inc.\n2\nTERMINOLOGY\nThe following acronyms are used in this guide. ACRONYM DEFINITION\nHCT Hosting Capacity Tool\nPST Pre-Screening Tool(s) – various tools, such as the HCT, which will  ...    Model Representation of the transmission, generation, and load elements of the interconnected SPP Transmission System and the transmission \nsystem of other regions in the Eastern Interconnection Area An electrical system or systems bounded by interconnection metering and telemetry, capable of controlling generation to maintain its interchange schedule with other Control Areas and contributing to \nfrequency regulation of the interconnection Bus A node on a branch\nKV Kilovolts\nMW Megawatts\nTransmission Lines Power lines present within the SPP footprint Generators A power generation facility\nPOI Point of interconnection Contour A heatmap representing power usage levels in various areas\nUI User Interface\nSouthwest Power Pool, Inc.\n3  ...    • Contingency Element\n• Available Capacity – In MW, on Monitored Facility for Contingent Element equals  ...    Where is the test environment? Access to the Test Environment: pst.itesppmembers.org.  ...    What do the colors represent? The colors"
